<HEADLINE> Police Detain 49 for Anti-Israel Demonstration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Police on Friday detained 49
men who demonstrated against an Israeli team taking part in an
ongoing cricket tournament in Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators aged between 20 and 48 were arrested at a
mosque near the University Malaya's main gate in Petaling Jaya
adjacent to the capital city after the afternoon Friday prayer,
according to the Malaysian national news agency Bernama.
</P>
<P>
About 500 demonstrators comprising university students and
opposition Parti (party) Islam Se Malaya (PAS) members assembled
near the university gate soon after Muslims finished the Friday
prayer at the mosque.
</P>
<P>
Policemen were deployed there earlier after authorities
received information of an impending demonstration near the
university.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad described the
demonstration as "stupid".
</P>
<P>
"This is a stupid act. We want to show the Israelis that
Muslims are right thinking people but with this act, the objective
is not met," Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad was quoted by Bernama
as saying in Kota Baharu, about 475 kilometers northeast of here.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said the demonstration would not have any effect on
the Palestinian-Israeli issue "because if they go to any Arab
country they will see similar actions.
</P>
<P>
"We want to show that Muslims in Malaysia can do things without
being too emotional, but now these people go and demonstrate, this
is stupid," Mahathir said.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir told reporters there that while Malaysia did not have
diplomatic ties with Israel, it wanted to get especially the
younger Israelis to oppose hardliners like Israel's Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
He said holding demonstrations would not in any way benefit the
Palestinian struggle but instead only served to encourage the two
sides to go on fighting.
</P>
<P>
"It's easy for us to demonstrate and seek a continuation of the
war between the Jews and Palestinians because we are not the ones
going to war.
</P>
<P>
"We live here and it's easy to demonstrate because we know that
nobody shoots us if we demonstrate in Malaysia but in other
countries you get shot if you hold demonstrations," he was quoted
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators were advised to stop their protests as their
actions did not help the peace process between the Palestinians
and the Israelis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
