<HEADLINE> Rain Forces Postponement of Davis Cup Tie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 4 (Xinhua) -- A Davis Cup Asia-Oceania zone
group two tie between Pakistan and Singapore was put off here
Friday because of the rain.
</P>
<P>
If Weather permitting, the opening singles and doubles will be
played on Saturday, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
In the singles, Singapore's Ho Kuen Yiep Fredrik will meet Umer
Rashid while another Sinaporean Sherman Lim will play against
Hamidul Haq.
</P>
<P>
The two Singaporeans will team up in the doubles to face
Pakistan's Asim Shafik and Nasir Shirazi. 
</P>
