<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait Stock Trading in First Qaurter Reaches 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Trading in Kuwait Stock
Market reached 2.4 billion Kuwaiti dinars (8 billion U.S. dollars)
in the first quarter of this year, 80 percent up compared with
that of the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The weekly report by Al-Shall Consultancy Group, which was
issued today, said that the value of daily dealings in the first
three months of this year averaged some 87 million dollars
comparing with 48.33 million dollars in the corresponding period
of 1996.
</P>
<P>
It said 1996 was a very active year for the Kuwaiti stock
market by all standards. Total dividends distributions for 1996
will reach 208.7 million dinars (688.7 million dollars), it added.
</P>
<P>
The cash transactions amounted to 128,245 dinars (423,209
dollars) with an average daily rate of 1,394 dinars (4,600
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Al-Shall said the number of listed companies in the bourse
rose to 61 with their value of shares estimated at 6.5 billion
dinars (21.45 billion Dollars).
</P>
<P>
The bourse administration agreed to list four other companies,
which are expected to start trading in the second quarter of this
year.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, only nationals of the Gulf Cooperation Council
states -- Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, the United Arab Emirates, Oman,
Qatar and Bahrain -- are allowed to trade shares in the Kuwait
Stock Exchange Market, which has been very active since last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
