<HEADLINE> France Urges Zairean Rebels to Respect Humanitarian Right </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 4 (Xinhua) -- France today called on the Zairean
rebels led by Laurent-Desire Kabila to report "humanitarian
right" and start immediately negotiations with the new Zairean
government of Prime Minister Etienne Tshisekedi.
</P>
<P>
"The ADFLC (Alliance of Democratic Forces for the Liberation
of Congo) should respect the humanitarian right and let the rescue
arrive at the innocent victims of the conflict," said French
Foreign Ministry spokesman Yves Doutriaux.
</P>
<P>
The Zairean rebels have refused to recognize the government of
Tshisekedi, who was nominated by President Mobutu Sese Seko on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"It is urgent that the inter-Zairean negotiations begin
effectively and that the cease-fire establish in an accompanying
way, so that the public engagement will be taken by Zaireans
themselves," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Direct negotiations between the two warring sides of Zaire is
supposed to begin in the next few days in South Africa under the
mediation of the special envoy of the United Nations and the
Organization of African Unity, Mohammed Sahnoun.
</P>
<P>
France once again has expressed its total support to the peace
mission of Sahnoun.  
</P>
</TEXT>
