<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lille's Garcion Tests Positive for Doping: Paper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Lille's midfielder David Garcion
tested positive for anabolic steroids, the first time a French
professional soccer player being caught for the performance
enhancing substance, a sports newspaper reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
L'Equipe said Garcion failed a drug test following a match
against Nice last December.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time a player in the French first division
league has tested positive for the muscle building drug, the daily
said.
</P>
<P>
L'Equipe said according to relevant rules, Garcion could be
suspended for nine months.
</P>
<P>
Garcion has reportedly appealed the test findings and will
continue to play for Lille until a verdict is reached by the
special commission of the French soccer federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
