special visit to Guangdong Province at the invitation of the
Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
Officials with the Guangdong Provincial Foreign Economic
Relations and Trade Commission, Merchants Bureau and relevant
enterprises held talks this afternoon with Eritrean guests,
discussing bilateral investment, and exchanges of cooperation in
economic and trade fields.
</P>
<P>
Lu Ruihua, governor of the province, met with and entertained
the visiting president and his party. Lu briefed the guests on
Guangdong's economic and social development, saying that
Guangdong's fast economic development in recent years can be
attributed to its efforts to use large amounts of foreign
investment, which contributed greatly to its industrialization.
</P>
<P>
The governor said its industrial output value has far exceeded
that of agriculture, and Guangdong, a former agricultural
province, has become an industrial one.
</P>
<P>
