<HEADLINE> Malaysian Premier Arrives in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad arrived in Kuwait today on a three-day
official visit during which he will sign an agreement to
avoid double taxation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He was welcomed by Kuwaiti acting Prime Minister and
Foreign Minister Sheikh Sabah Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah and other
officials at the international airport.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir was accompanied by an 11-member delegation including
some government officials and several top businessmen. This is his
first visit to Kuwait since he became the prime minister
in 1981.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir will hold talks with Kuwaiti Amir Sheikh Jaber
Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah and other government officials on means of
fostering bilateral ties in all domains.
</P>
<P>
Besides signing the agreement of avoiding double taxation,
Mahathir will also discuss bilateral trade relations with Kuwaiti
leaders, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and Malaysia established diplomatic ties in May 1963.
The two countries are linked with deep-rooted historic political
and economic relations, the sources said. 
</P>
