<HEADLINE> 30 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Thirty rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in the operations staged
by the Turkish security forces in southeastern Turkey, an official
statement reported today.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of Emergency Regional Rule
said that the Turkish government troops Friday wiped out 26 PKK
militants in Kigi town of Bingol province and four others near
Aydogdu police station in Silopi town of Sirnak province bordering
northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, five soldiers of the Turkish security forces died in
the conflicts with the PKK guerrillas, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
It also said that two PKK rebels surrendered to the security
forces in the provinces of Sirnak and Hakkari.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 12-year-old separatist war for
self-rule, which has claimed over 21,000 lives in the southeast of
Turkey since August 1984. 
</P>
