<HEADLINE> Shanghai, San Francisco Building Up Sisterly Friendship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai and its American sister
city on the other side of the Pacific Ocean, San Francisco, signed
up for more cooperative projects today to further tighten their
bond this year and next.
</P>
<P>
According to a memorandum of friendly exchanges in 1997-1998
signed here today, San Francisco's Pacific Stock Exchange will
provide internships for managers of the Shanghai Stock Exchange,
and the two cities will also sponsor the sixth training course on
international business management.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Shanghai will build a pavilion in San Francisco to
mark their sisterly relations. Shanghai will also send some
technicians to San Francisco to learn about the city's
long-distance water supply systems.
</P>
<P>
They also decided to jointly conduct in research for treatment
of burns, cardiovascular diseases, and women's and children's
health care.
</P>
<P>
They became sister cities in 1980, and since then have carried
out 125 cooperative projects.
</P>
<P>
Willie Brown, mayor of San
Francisco, and his Shanghai counterpart Xu Kuangdi attended the
signing ceremony of the memorandum. 
</P>
</TEXT>
