<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Says Russian-Belarusian Treaty Path to Integration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
said today in a national radio address that the Russian-Belarusian
Union Treaty opened up the path to real integration.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said that the living standard of the two countries
would not decline after the union, and that Russia would help
Belarus to catch up.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that forming a union with Belarus did not mean
that Russia would stand apart from other neighbors grouped in the
Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS), or that "their problems
are becoming something secondary to us."
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin and his Belarusian counterpart, Alexander Lukashenko,
signed a Union Treaty on Wednesday. 
