<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Leader Arrives in Rome </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing
Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC), arrived
here today for a six-day official visit to Italy following his
trip to Norway.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, who is the first Chinese NPC leader to visit Italy, was
greeted at the airport by Vice President of the Italian Senate
Ersilia Salvato.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said in an airport statement that his visit is aimed at
deepening understanding, enhancing friendship and improving
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that since China established diplomatic ties with Italy
26 years ago, bilateral relations have been developing smoothly,
thanks to frequent high-level exchanges and friendly cooperation
in politics, economy, culture and science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that building a stable long-term Sino-Italian
relationship for the 21st century will benefit not only the two
countries but also world peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
Italy is the third leg of Qiao's European and Asian tour, which
also took him to France. He is expected to hold talks with Italian
leaders on bilateral and international issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
