<HEADLINE> Chinese Top leaders Join Two Million in Tree Planting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
joined two million Beijing residents here today to take part in
the annual nationwide voluntary tree-planting day.
</P>
<P>
On the bright sunny morning, Jiang and other senior Chinese
leaders Li Peng, Li Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing and Hu
Jintao, came to south Beijing's Park of the Temple of Heaven,
where they were joined by dozens of school children carrying
buckets.
</P>
<P>
Jiang planted two pine trees, shovelling the soil with a
spade. Three students helped him water the newly-planted trees.
</P>
<P>
The Park of the Temple of Heaven is known for its vast spread
of well-preserved evergreens; at least 4,000 of them were planted
hundreds of years ago.
</P>
<P>
"Tree planting and afforestation represents an important
undertaking that benefits the country and people a great deal,"
Jiang noted in planting the trees. "The entire nation must be
mobilized to continue this endeavor."
</P>
<P>
Since China launched its annual nationwide voluntary
tree-planting day 16 years ago, a total of 25 billion trees have
been planted throughout the country. The percentage of forest
cover in the country has reached 13.93 percent.
</P>
<P>
The yearly tree-planting day falls on the first Saturday of
April. At least two million Beijing residents planted trees in and
around the city today.
</P>
<P>
"This warm and blooming Spring day is the best time for tree
planting," Premier Li said, while watering a pine just
planted. "As the national capital, Beijing should be cleaner and
prettier."
</P>
<P>
Beijing is among the best forested cities in the country, with
a percentage of forest cover reaching 32 percent, according to the
Ministry of Forestry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
