<HEADLINE> Diamond Capital in Central Zaire Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Forces of the rebel Alliance of
Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Congo-Zaire (ADFL) today
entered zaire's diamond capital of mbuji-mayi in central Zaire, a
report reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Mining sources in the town said rebels had streamed in across
a bridge in the morning.
</P>
<P>
``People are cheering in the streets, there's a heck of a lot
of noise. they are treating this as very good news,'' one said.
</P>
<P>
The rebels took up arms to topple President Mobutu Sese Seko
last October. They repulsed an offensive launched by government
troops in February and seized Kisengani, the third largest city
in Zaire and vowed to take Lubumbashi in Shaba Province this
month
</P>
<P>
The mining capital of Mbuji-Mayi and the surrounding Kasai
region of central Zaire is a diamond-rich land of opposition to
President Mobutu. Kasai even uses different money to defy the
ailing president and is a crucial test of support for the rebel
alliance. 
</P>
