<HEADLINE> American ESSO Opens First Lubricating Oil Plant in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Construction started Thursday in
the Tianjin Port Development Zone on the first lubricating oil
mixing plant in China, financed by U.S.'s ESSO Petroleum Company.
</P>
<P>
ESSO will invest more than 25 million U.S. dollars on the
plant, designed with an annual capacity of 36,000 tons of
lubricating oil and scheduled to go into operation in 1998, said
Kho Hong Chuan, chairman of the ESSO Tianjin Company Ltd.
</P>
<P>
He announced that construction of a second lubricating oil
plant with the same capacity will start later this month in the
city of Ningbo, east China's Zhejiang Province, and be completed
by the end of 1998.
</P>
<P>
New technology will be applied in the two plants to promote
ESSO's competitiveness in providing lubricating oil and special
oils of high quality, he said.
</P>
<P>
The company pledged to provide technical and sales services for
Chinese consumers, through its bureaus in Beijing, Shanghai,
Guangzhou, Chengdu, Harbin and Hong Kong. 
</P>
