The magazine quoted Graf saying that although it hurt to agree
to the deal, it was worth it to avoid further litigation and put
the "medai circus" behind her to focus on tennis.
</P>
<P>
Graf, 27, recently lost her ranking as world number one women's
tennis player to 16-year-old Martina Hingis of Switzerland after
94 weeks on top.
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors, who had probed Graf's finances for nearly two
years, dropped their investigation last month after she agreed to
pay a sum to charity. The amount was not made public at the time.
</P>
<P>
Steffi Graf denied she had done anything illegal in handling
her finances. 
