<HEADLINE> All-Star Teams to Perform to Mark HK's Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 4 (Xinhua) -- A first ever all-star team of
the International Football Federation (FIFA) will clash with an
all-star side from the Asian Football confederation (AFC) on July
3 this year to mark the handover of Hong Kong back to China at the
 midnight on June 30.
</P>
<P>
The initiative of the celebration match, named as Reunification
 Cup, between the all-star teams of FIFA and AFC was raised by
Henry Fok, President of the Sports Community for Celebration of
Reunification of Hong Kong with China and President of the Hong
Kong Football Association (HKFA).
</P>
<P>
The idea won full support from both the FIFA and AFC, the
sport's world and Asian governing bodies.
</P>
<P>
Among the FIFA All-Stars players are George Weah from Liberia,
who in 1996 was named Africa, European and World Player of the
Year, Alan Shearer, England's first-choice striker and captain
who, after finishing as the top scorer in Euro'96, was signed by
Newcastle for 15 million pounds sterling, and Lothar Matthaeus,
who led Germany to the World Cup in 1990 and was named as the 1990
and 1991 FIFA's Players of the Year.
</P>
<P>
The AFC Asian All-Stars side include such ace players in the
region as Mohammed Al Daeyea, a Saudi Arabian goalkeeper who was
named the best defender in the 1996 Asian Cup, Fan Zhiyi, captain
of China's national team and the nation's best player in 1995 and
1996, South Korean Hwang Sun-hong, the top scorer in the 1994
Asian Games and a regular striker of the South Korean national
team, and Hao Haidong, China's ace midfielder.
</P>
<P>
Hosts Hong Kong has its best defender Chan Chi-keong listed in
the All-Stars side.
</P>
<P>
The FIFA All-Stars team is to be led by Josef Venglos from the
Czech Republic and coached by Bora Milutinovic from Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The AFC Asian All-Stars squad is to be led by Henry Fok and AFC
Secretary General Peter Velappan and coached by Kwok Ka-ming, Hong
Kong's head coach.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
