<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Government Achieves Budget Balance in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The Macao government achieved a
balanced budget in 1996, resulting in 24 million patacas (about
3.04 million US dollars) of budget surplus, the Macao government
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The total income of the government reached 8.836 billion
patacas (about 1.118 billion US dollars), down one percent from
1995, mainly due to a decrease of income from casinos.
</P>
<P>
The overall expenditure topped 8.812 billion patacas (about
1.115 billion US dollars). Of the total expenditure, the
government organs spent 6.5 billion patacas (about 822.8 million
US dollars), up 6.6 percent from 1995, a result of salary increase
for government employees, according to a press release from the
office of the Social Affairs and Budgetary Secretary.
</P>
<P>
The cost of public investment and development in 1996 hit 1.3
billion patacas (about 164,6 million US dollars), an increase of
7.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The release said that the government no longer owes direct
debts as it paid off two loans in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The government said it will pay back all indirect debts the
government owes, namely the government's guarantee of loans for
the Macao International Airport, which reached 489 million patacas
(about 61.9 million US dollars), before December 19, 1999.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
