<HEADLINE> Technical Renovation of Old Chinese Industrial Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning Province in northeast
China has launched a technical renovation project for industrial
revival by making enterprises the major technology developers.
</P>
<P>
It also calls for large and medium-sized state-owned
enterprises to develop their own patented and name-brand products,
and for technological progress to be the major way to improve the
province's economy.
</P>
<P>
The project's target for this year is the development of 6,500
new products, 450 of which should be at an advanced level, and
1,800 with advanced domestic standards. In addition, the new
products are expected to produce an output value of 25 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Over the next five years, every enterprise in this old
industrial base will be required to develop a new product on its
own and one with a research institute. Enterprises are being asked
to focus on products and technology with market prospects.
</P>
<P>
According to government officials, policies will be made and
measures taken to ensure the smooth operation of the project.
</P>
</TEXT>
