<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-05 08:44 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Scientists Research on Bacterial Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Israeli researchers have
discovered a molecule that enables bacteria to resist an
unusually wide range of drugs, according to a report of the
Weizman Institute of Science published here today.
</P>
<P>
The find, reported in the April issue of the Journal of
Bacteriology, suggests it may become more and more difficult to
design effective new medications for bacterial infections.
</P>
<P>
On the brighter side, the newly-identified molecule, named
MdfA, may serve as a model for the further study and
understanding of multidrug resistance, aiding efforts to overcome
this phenomenon in bacterial diseases.
</P>
<P>
This research may also help clarify multidrug resistance in
human cancers, which results in tumor cells expelling anti-cancer
drugs, thus presenting serious obstacles to chemotherapy.
</P>
<P>
"The more sophisticated the drugs we develop, the more
bacteria may emerge equipped with sophisticated ways to fight
these drugs," says Dr. Eitan Bibi of the institute's
Biochemistry Department, who conducted the study with doctoral
student Rotem Edgar.
</P>
<P>
In the report, Bibi predicts, "This is an obvious challenge
for antibacterial therapies that must be planned in anticipation
of growing resistance mechanisms." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970405.0106 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Urumqi Zoo Has Another Snow Leopard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The snow leopard population at the
Urumqi Zoo, in the capital of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region, has risen from four to five at a cost of over
20 sheep of a herdsman.
</P>
<P>
Not long ago, Eziz, a herdsman of the Taxkorgan Tajik
Autonomous County on the Pamirs, came upon three snow leopards
munching on three sheep from his fold. Two of the leopards fled
when they saw him, while the third, a cub, was trapped in the
sheep pen.
</P>
<P>
Knowing that the snow leopard is a state-protected rare
wildlife, Eziz sent his son rushing to the township seat on the
horseback to file a report. The ride took six days. By the time
officials arrived at Eziz's home, 20 sheep had been killed by the
snow leopard.
</P>
<P>
As the traffic between Eziz's home and the county was blocked
by ice and snow, and two snow-covered steeps 6,000 m above the sea
level need to be climbed over, his son spent more than half a
month sending the cat to the county's wildlife protection
department, with the help of local herdsmen.
</P>
<P>
With the approval of the Ministry of Forestry, the Urumqi Zoo
shipped the leopard back from Taxkorgan County, some 1,900 km
southwest of Urumqi.
</P>
<P>
According to Fan Jiang, deputy director of the Urumqi Zoo
Administrative Office, the male snow leopard weighs some 30
kg. Its neck and claws were wounded and it was under the
meticulous care of medical workers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
