<HEADLINE> Iran Provides Assistance to Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Iran announced here today that
1,750 tonnes of Iranian humanitarian assistance arrived in
Afghanistan Friday.
</P>
<P>
This was the third consignment of the Iranian aid to the
war-torn country in the past two months, the state-run Tehran
Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the food consignment will be distributed
among people in the northern and central parts of Afghanistan
subsequent to delivery to the representatives of various factions
there.
</P>
<P>
However, the report did not mention how the assistance
reached the northern and central regions in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
It said that the previous two consignments included 1,900
tonnes of flour along with other food essentials which were also
distributed among people in the two regions.
</P>
<P>
Iran declared earlier that it will continue to provide
"humanitarian aid" to Afghanistan since it still recognizes
ousted Afghan President Burhanuddin Rabbani as the legitimate
representative of the country.
</P>
<P>
Late last October, a conference on Afghanistan was held in
Iran without participation of any Afghan groups. 
</P>
</TEXT>
