<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Invests 240 Million Dollars for Ambitious Science Projects (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The proposed new machine will operate at energy levels from
2.2 to 2.5 GeV, to provide a brighter source of synchrotron light
for researchers in fields ranging from advanced materials, life
sciences, nuclear physics, medical science to electronics,
medicine, petroleum and the chemical industries," researchers from
CAS said.
</P>
<P>
"The country hopes that the appliance of frontier science will
give itself a firm foothold in the forefront of international
scientific and technological science in the coming century," Lu
said.
</P>
<P>
China will invest 120 million yuan to build an earth crust
movement monitoring network, by adopting a global satellite
positioning system, and satellite laser distance measurement
know-how.
</P>
<P>
"This indicates that China will possibly make some major
progress in earthquake forecast," a researcher from CAS said.
</P>
<P>
China will also develop a micro-precise monitoring system,
using satellites, that will pave the way for scientific and
technological advances in the coming century.
</P>
<P>
"In order to carry out the plan smoothly and more effectively,"
scientists said, "China will draw on experience collected from its
building of atomic and hydrogen bombs in the 1960s and 1970s, and
arouse the most elite scientists. It will also strengthen
international cooperation, and win strong support from scientific
and industrial circles."
</P>
<P>
CAS will get most of the financial support from the central
government budget. And local governments of Shanghai municipality
and Guangdong province have offered their financial support to the
building of Shanghai synchrontron light source and a state-of-art
research vessel.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, scientific researchers in Hong Kong also expressed
their interest in joining the construction of synchrontron
device.  
</P>
</TEXT>
