<HEADLINE> Northwest China Province to Develop Township Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Qinghai province
plans to spend as much as 2.2 billion yuan developing local
township enterprises this year, 700 million yuan more than in 1996.
</P>
<P>
About 800 million yuan of the amount will be used for 493
new and extension projects and for technological improvements.
</P>
<P>
The province expects to build up three counties with a billion
yuan each in output value from township enterprises, and two with
output value reaching 500 million each, and 12 towns and
enterprises with output value reaching 100 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
It also plans to construct 20 township industrial zones to
advance the development of the provincial township enterprises,
which will give priority to small-sized hydro-electric power
stations, processing of farm and sideline produce, plantations,
livestock raising, and animal husbandry,
</P>
<P>
Provincial township enterprises earned more than 2.94 billion
yuan last year, a nearly 32.5 percent rise from the previous
year. During the 1991-1995 period, they had an annual growth of
more than 30 percent.  
</P>
