<HEADLINE> Fire Destroys 2 Ships in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- A big fire destroyed two ships and
damaged another one today at a port in Zamboanga city in the
southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Three crew members suffered from burns and had been sent to
nearby hospitals. It was feared that some of their companions
could have died aboard.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate reports about the damage of property but
it is estimated to reach millions of pesos.
</P>
<P>
The fire started with an explosion at the engine room of a
wooden ship loaded with liquid fuel and cooking gas when a crew
member started the engine early this morning.
</P>
<P>
The blaze caused dozens of explosions that were heard from as
far as seven kilometers away before the ship was consumed by the
fire and sank three hours later.
</P>
<P>
A research vessel of the Department of Science and Technology
which anchored nearby also caught fire and was totally destroyed.
</P>
<P>
City Fire Marshall Roman Apolinario said the firefighters could
not combat the blaze fueled by exploding gasoline, diesel,
petroleum and liquefied petroleum gas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
