<HEADLINE> Chongqing to Host National Stamp Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The China 1997 stamp exhibition,
the country's seventh, is to be held from October 18 to 24 in
Chongqing municipality in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time the city has hosted a national big
cultural activity since it was promoted to a municipality, to mark
the 175th anniversary of local postal service and the 100th
anniversary of the founding of the local postal bureau.
</P>
<P>
The previous six national stamp shows were held in Beijing and
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Stamps at the show, which will be divided into 11 categories,
will be provided by members from philatelic associations
nationwide. Some of the exhibits will compete for eight awards.
</P>
<P>
Overseas philatelists will be invited to attend the showcase
event, which is expected to help the country make preparations for
hosting an international philatelic exhibition in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The show will be sponsored by the All-China Philatelic
Federation and the local post offices with the approval of the
Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
