<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Export Increases in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' export value for
the first two months of this year increased by 16.2 percent to
3.503 billion U.S. dollars from 3.014 billion dollars during the
same period of 1996, the Philippine National Statistics Office
said today.
</P>
<P>
Receipts from merchandise exports for February alone reached
1.811 billion dollars, surpassing last year's revenue by 13.6
percent, the office said in a press statement.
</P>
<P>
The office said that electronics and components remained the
country's biggest foreign exchange earner with income for February
rising by 22.1 percent over a year ago, accounting for 41.9
percent of the aggregate export revenue.
</P>
<P>
But exports of articles of apparel and clothing accessories,
the second biggest export products in the country, declined by 8.4
percent in the month, it said.
</P>
<P>
The office said that receipts from input and output peripheral
units, representing 7 percent of the total exports, increased by
575.6 percent to 126.8 million dollars from 18.77 million dollars
a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The United States continued to be the Philippines' biggest
export market, followed by Japan, the Netherlands and Singapore.
</P>
</TEXT>
