<HEADLINE> Australia Wins Davis Cup Quarter Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 5 (Xinhua) -- World top-ranked pair Todd
Woodbridge and Mark Woodforde gave Australia a 3-0 quarter final
Davis Cup win against the Czech Republic in Adelaide, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Czech duo Martin Damm and David Rikl surprised their hosts by
taking the first set before going down 4-6, 6-1, 7-5, 6-4 on the
grass center court.
</P>
<P>
Pat Rafter and Mark Philippoussis both won their singles
rubbers on Friday to set Australia on the way to a semi-final
meeting with either the United States or the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge was Australia's weak link in the opening set, twice
dropping his serve to allow the unfancied Czech pair an ideal
start.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will play two reverse dead singles rubbers on
Sunday. Australia upset Davis Cup holders France, also on grass,
in the previous round two months ago in Sydney. 
</P>
</TEXT>
