<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Afforestation Efforts Enhanced in Northeast Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Jilin province
has enhanced its afforestation efforts in order to improve its
ecology and contribute to economic development.
</P>
<P>
Jilin province has one of China's richest forest resources, and
afforestation has long been a high priority for the provincial
government.
</P>
<P>
Starting last year, the departments in Jilin gradually enhanced
their work in urban and rural land greening, built tree-planting
bases for volunteers, economic forestry planting, and construction
of green shelterbelt systems.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate that 42 large tree-planting bases for
volunteers were established in the province last year, with 64
million trees planted.
</P>
<P>
"Last year we have also built five green economic development
belts by planting 23,000 hectare of economic forests, which helped
the farmers to become well to do," said an official from the
forestry department of the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the forest coverage in Jilin
province is expected to reach 44 percent in the near future.
</P>
</TEXT>
