<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Hold World Computer Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam will hold a world computer
exhibition in Ho Chi Minh City between April 23 and April 26,
local reports said today.
</P>
<P>
On display at the exhibition will be the latest software,
hardware, networking and peripheral products from leading
manufacturers worldwide with a special emphasis on banking,
CAD/CAM and automation, networking and multimedia products.
</P>
<P>
During the show, computer managers, experts and operators will
have a chance to exchange experience and solutions about the
latest computer developments as well as the relevant projects in
Vietnam, both at the national and local levels.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has become one of the most rapidly developing markets
of computer in the region thanks to stable economic development
and soaring demand for computers, said Vietnamese officials.
</P>
<P>
The market in Vietnam is expected to exceed one billion
U.S. dollars by the year 2000, they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
