<HEADLINE> Germany Not to Support Tamil Rebels: State Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Visiting German State Minister
</P>
<P>
for Foreign Affairs Dr. Werner Hoyer has stated that the
German government would not provide any support to the Tamil
rebels, directly or indirectly, according to official sources here
today.
</P>
<P>
The German minister Friday was met by Prime Minister Sirimavo
Bandaranaike and held talks on the bilateral relations between the
two countries with Sri Lankan Foreign Minister Lakshman
Kadirgamar.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, he said that "We are ready to ban the LTTE
(the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam) and deport its members from
our country if there is adequate evidence that they are engaged in
terrorist activities," the sources said.
</P>
<P>
On Germany's aid programs for Sri Lanka, the sources quoted him
as saying that German government is to expand its programs
especially those operational in the North and East.
</P>
<P>
Germany has granted 5.8 million U.S. dollars to Sri Lanka for
rehabilitation programs in Jaffna peninsula where was once the
stronghold of the LTTE, who has waged a guerrilla war for a
separate state in the island country since 1983.  
</P>
</TEXT>
