<HEADLINE> Russian Duma Supports Reunification with Belarus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Russia's State Duma today called
for the gradual reunification of Russia and Belarus, the Itar-Tass
news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The lower house adopted a statement outlining the goals and
principles of the creation of the Russian-Belarussian federation
as a unified sovereign democratic republican state.
</P>
<P>
"The deepening economic, social and political crisis in all
spheres of public and state life in both countries" has prompted
the need for the reunification of Russia and Belarus, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
The Duma also passed a resolution condemning coverage of the
creation of the Russian-Belarusian union by Russia's mass media,
primarily television and radio.
</P>
<P>
Lawmakers urged the president and government to take immediate
measures against media criticism of the union treaty, even going
so far as cutting off financing for television and radio companies
and periodicals.
</P>
<P>
The State Duma also called on the heads of television and radio
companies and other mass media bodies to work for the unification
of the two peoples and states.
</P>
<P>
The treaty forming a union between Russia and Belarus was
signed by Russian President Boris Yeltsin and his Belarussian
counterpart Alexander Lukashenko last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chairman of Russia's upper house of parliament Yegor
Stroyev and Belarussian Foreign Minister Ivan Antonovich said
Thursday that the ultimate aim of the treaty was the unification
of the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
