<HEADLINE> Half of Young People in Southern Italy Are Unemployed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 4 (Xinhua) -- More than half of the young people in
Italy's economically depressed south, the so-called Mezzogiorno,
are jobless, official statistics showed.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment among young people in the north is 55.9 percent,
against a national average of 34 percent and 19.6 percent in the
north and 33.8 percent in central Italy, the latest quarterly data
from the National Statistic Bureau (Istat) here show.
</P>
<P>
General unemployment figures are also serious in the south,
particularly in the Campania region, whose capital is
Naples. General unemployment there is 26.6 percent, compared with
a national average of 12.4 percent and 21.8 percent for the
Mezzogiorno as a whole. The unemployment rate in the north is 7.1
percent and in central Italy it stands at 10.6 percent. 
</P>
