<HEADLINE> HK Toys Attract Many Buyers at Tokyo Toy Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's toys had caught the
attention of many buyers at the recent Tokyo Toy Show by the
quality, innovative design and price competitiveness of the
products offered by the Hong Kong manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC)
said here today that a delegation of 20 Hong Kong toy
manufacturers under the auspices of the TDC exhibited a vast array
of toys at the show, including children's tents, electronic games,
bicycles, wind-up savings banks, plastic play sets, stuffed
animals and protective pads.
</P>
<P>
He said that a total of 87,000 buyers visited the Tokyo Toy
Fair which was held from March 19 to 23 at the Tokyo International
Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Kazuji Kodaira, assistant general manager of the trade
operation department for Tomy Tec Co., Ltd., commented: "Hong Kong
products are priced very attractively and their quality seems to
be equal to Japanese products, adding, "I think Hong Kong toys are
marketable in Japan."
</P>
<P>
Naoki Kobayashi of Seiko Epson said that his company already is
doing business with Hong Kong toy makers. The key to the success
of Hong Kong toys is their price competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Japan imported 5 billion HK dollars (642 million US
dollars) worth of toys, dolls and games from Hong Kong, up 20
percent over last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
