Top-seeded World Open champion Sarah Fitz-Gerald
required only 29 minutes to reach the women's semi-finals,
beating fellow Australian Liz Irving 9-1, 9-3, 9-2.
</P>
<P>
Fitz-Gerald next plays the British national champion Sue
Wright, who won in straight games against her compatriot Linda
Charman, 9-7, 9-5, 9-4.
</P>
<P>
The men's defending champion and world number one Jansher Khan
also won in straight games over England number one Chris Walker
15-5, 15-9, 15-12.
</P>
<P>
Jansher's next plays the 19-year-old Egyptian Ahmed Barada who
advanced after beating Australian Dan Jenson 14-15, 12-15,
15-13, 15-10, 15-12. 
