<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northern Chinese Province Attracting Foreign Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, April 5 (Xinhua) -- North China's Shanxi province,
which has a major share of China's coal output, saw improvements
in foreign funding last year, with 1.8 billion US dollars worth
coming to the province.
</P>
<P>
This was as much as the total for the previous 10 years, and it
brought the province up from 23rd to 15th place in use of foreign
funds.
</P>
<P>
Construction work on the Yangcheng Power Plant, the largest
jointly funded thermo-electric power plant in China, started in
Shanxi last year. It is expected to require 900 million US dollars
in foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
Also in the works is the Wanjiazhai water project, which is
expected to greatly alleviate the province's water shortage, with
500 million US dollars worth of World Bank and foreign government
loans being used.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture is the most active sector in utilizing foreign
funds. The province has forged ties with more than 30 countries
and regions. By the end of last year, the agricultural sector had
utilized 478 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Last year, it had received nearly 100,000 Chinese and overseas
tourists, bringing it 26.67 million US dollars worth of foreign
currency earnings. Some 10,000 business people from more than 100
countries and regions also visited the province last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
