<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits Nicaragua's Pacific Coast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.8 on the
Richter scale rocked Nicaragua's Pacific coast early today but no
casualties or serious damage were reported.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake happened at about 12:49 a.m. local time (06:49
GMT) in the Pacific Ocean and was felt in the capital Managua 60
kilometers away to the north, where buildings shook but no one was
reported injured, the Nicaraguan Institute of Territorial Studies
said.
</P>
<P>
The institute said the tremor was caused by the meeting of the
Cocos and Caribe tectonic plates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
