<HEADLINE> Spain Takes Four Golds in Opening Day of EU Weightlifting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Spanish lifters claimed four out
of eight gold medals on offer on the first day of the European
Union Weightlifting Tournament in Pori, Finland on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In the men's 54-kg category, Alfonso Portillo won the crown for
Spain with a snatch of 102.5 and a jerk of 130 for a total of
232.5 kilograms.
</P>
