<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zone for Agricultural Hi-Tech Development to Be Built in Yangling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 5 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Yangling
Demonstration Zone for Hi-tech Agricultural Industries officially
kicked off Friday in Yangling, Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
It is the only State-level zone designated for agricultural
hi-tech development, according to "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
The zone will serve as a national high-tech research center. It
will specialize in turning research into practical production
uses, according to Cheng Andong, governor of Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The State Council officially approved the plan on March 25. In
1934, China's first agricultural school was established in
Yangling.
</P>
<P>
Yangling is a small town 90 km west of Xi'an, the provincial
capital. The development zone will encompass 20 sq km. Some units
will be located elsewhere in Shaanxi in order to conduct
demonstrations throughout the province.
</P>
<P>
First to be put into operation will be several State key
laboratories and research and development centers for
drought-resistant wheat seed, water-conserving irrigation
techniques and soil conservation. These are regarded as vital
problems to be solved in the development of agriculture in
Northwest China, Cheng said.
</P>
<P>
Yangling, China's largest agricultural research and education
center, concentrates more than 4,000 agricultural scientists and
experts engaged in 64 disciplines and programmes of agriculture,
forestry and hydraulic engineering.
</P>
<P>
The town has two universities, five research institutes and
three special schools for agricultural sciences.
</P>
<P>
Since the founding of new China in 1949, more than 60,000
agricultural-scientific personnel have been trained. Some 5,000
agricultural research achievements have been made, recouping 200
billion yuan (24.1 billion US dollars) in agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Yangling has co-operated with and set up
academic exchanges with more than 20 countries. At least 30
international projects underprinted with investments of some 8
million US dollars are now being undertaken, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
To speed construction of the zone, the central and local
governments have invested nearly 200 million yuan (24.1 million
dollars) for its infrastructure, and 13 industries have been
established to attract domestic and foreign funds into the zone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
