<HEADLINE> Turkish Opposition Party Leader Dies of Heart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Turkish right-wing
Nationalist Action Party (MHP) Alparslan Turkes died of heart
attack in Ankara tonight, Turkish private TV Kanal D reported.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Turkes was rushed to the Bayindir Medical
Center, the most sophisticated hospital in Ankara, for emergency
treatment when he suffered a heart attack following his
participation in the MHP Congress of Amasya province near the
Black Sea.
</P>
<P>
However, doctors of the medical centers tried their best to
save his life to no avail.
</P>
<P>
Turkes, a father of seven, was born in Nicosia of Cyprus
in 1917 and served as deputy prime minister of Turkey between
1977 and 1978.
</P>
<P>
Turkes played an important role in the 1960 coup when he served
as colonel in the Turkish army. He acted as MHP leader since 1965
and was considered as one of the veteran political leaders in
Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
