<HEADLINE> Police Find Cocaine Hidden Among Bananas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 4 (Xinhua) -- State police found more than
1,100 pounds of cocaine hidden in a truckload of bananas in the
biggest drug bust in Alabama.
</P>
<P>
Police released the driver of the tractor-trailer after
concluding he did not know he was carrying drugs Thursday, the
Associated Press reported.
</P>
<P>
State troopers made the find while conducting safety
inspections on a highway. A drug dog sniffed out the cocaine,
which was wrapped in plastic in kilogram packages. Police
estimated the value at 24 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The truck was bound from Slidell, Louisiana, to New Jersey.
</P>
</TEXT>
